GEOL 308: Igneous and Metamorphic Petrology. 4 credits.
Practical and theoretical background for identifying, classifying and interpreting igneous and metamorphic rocks with emphasis on their petrogenesis and relationship to the tectonic context. May include field trips. Offered by Atmospheric/Oceanic/Earth Sci. Limited to three attempts.
Recommended Prerequisite: MATH 105 or higher
